A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
Commander, Marine Forces Cyber Command (COMMARFORCYBERCOM), as the Marine Corps service component commander for the Commander, U.S. Cyber
Command (CDRUSCYBERCOM), represents Marine Corps capabilities and interests; advises CDRUSCYBERCOM on the proper employment and support of Marine
Corps forces; and coordinates deployment, employment, and redeployment planning and execution of attached forces. MARFORCYBER provides highly skilled software
engineers with critical certification that support the implementation and creation of capabilities that enable automation of key system attributes and components. In
addition, these personnel provide support to Department of Defense Information Network systems, Defensive Cyberspace Operations systems, and global operations
in support of US Cyber Command. These software engineers are developing automation capabilities to identify and mitigate Common Vulnerabilities and Exposures
(CVEs) to ensure security of our network, to include our cloud migration, enable our cyber mission force operators to increase lethality against current operational
threats, and provide for increased response times to adversary threats to our friendly networks.

Adversarial Cyber Developmental Test and Evaluation: Provides mission based cyber risk assessment services to Marine Corps Systems Command (MCSC) programs
of record (PoRs) via Marine Corps Tactical Systems Support Activity (MCTSSA). MCTSSA serves as the Cyber Developmental Test and Evaluation agent in accordance
with DODI 8500.01, DODI 5000.02, and the DoD Cybersecurity Test and Evaluation Guidebook. MCTSSA conducts adversarial cyber assessments on programs of
record in development and prototypes to identify and mitigate vulnerabilities early in the acquisition cycle. These cyber assessments help inform program offices on
how to design cyber survivable systems. MCTSSA also develops tools and guidebooks to assist with designing cyber resilient networks and testing prototypes that will
enhance the security posture of information systems.

