Description: Maintain and perform hardware and software upgrades to the Effectiveness of Naval Electronic
Warfare (EW) Systems (ENEWS) inventory of flyable and shore based Anti-Ship Missile (ASM) Electro-
Optic/Infrared (EO/IR), Visible and Radio Frequency (RF) simulators and simulation systems. Perform
periodic evaluation of IR and RF simulators to assess simulation operational performance and collect data for
comparison with previously recorded data. Also includes development and maintenance of all simulator control
consoles, captive-carry pods and power supplies.

FY 2025 Plans:
- Continue to maintain custom instrumentation equipment such as digital data acquisition and ground truth
systems.
- Continue to maintain and upgrade 20 hardware simulators, 6 programmable simulators, and associated
simulator control panels to support system effectiveness evaluations for EW Program of Record (PORs) such
as SEWIP and AOEW. Maintenance and upgrades include integration of higher performance components for
increased reliability and improved mission performance. Installation of specialized wiring and cables in test
aircraft and maintaining flight certifications for captive-carry electronic pods.
- Complete field test preparation and certification for new simulation asset.
- Initiate process to package and properly store two legacy hardware simulators no longer required to be
maintained as part of the active inventory.
- Initiate and complete extensive system maintenance and upgrade for one RF hardware simulator.
- Initiate and complete fabrication of a hardware interface to conduct laboratory testing for one RF simulator.
- Initiate and complete software and hardware upgrades for four RF and two EO/IR simulators.
FY 2026 Base Plans:
- Continue to maintain custom instrumentation equipment such as digital data acquisition and ground truth
systems.
- Continue to maintain and upgrade 20 RF and EO/IR hardware simulators, 6 programmable simulators, and
associated simulator control panels to support system effectiveness evaluations for EW Program of Record
(PORs) such as SEWIP (V)6, (V)7, SOEA, and LEED. Maintenance and upgrades include integration of higher
performance components for increased reliability and improved mission performance. Installation of specialized
wiring and cables in test aircraft and maintaining flight certifications for captive-carry electronic pods.
- Complete packaging two legacy hardware simulators and place into storage.
- Initiate introduction of one new simulation asset into the ENEWS inventory, prepare and certify system for field
testing.

