C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                    FY 2025       FY 2026      FY 2027
Title: CEM                                                                                                                                 5.428         3.927        3.316
Description: Perform knowledge-based studies (KBS) — Develop/modernize cost datasets/databases, data collection process
improvements, analysis to develop new estimating methods/tools (e.g., statistical and modeling tools, cost estimating relationships
(CERs), schedule estimating relationships (SERs), technical estimating relationships (TERs)), and perform other gap filling studies
for aircraft, UAVs, ballistic and tactical missiles, munitions, advanced electronics, aircraft modifications, ground stations and
automated information systems, space systems, launch vehicles, and crosscutting areas.

Operational Systems Development

C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                   FY 2025    FY 2026       FY 2027
ACCOMPLISHMENTS:
- Updated the plan and resource summaries to complete cost research across all Air Force weapon system
commodities aligned to the SAF/FMC cost research plan.
- Continued to develop and share curated datasets and databases mapped into standard structures for use by the cost analysis
community.
- Developed through machine learning curated cost datasets and databases mapped into standard structures as part of the Cost
Analysis Data Operating Model effort, per the SAF/FM Strategic Plan.
- Scraped contract modifications data using scripts and prototyping this using large-language models. Employed this data to
develop benchmarks to estimate the cost of engineering change orders in the development and production phases of acquisition
programs.
- Collected historical program data to fill gaps against defined data collection requirements from previous year efforts and
integrated historical data collected into CADE system for central access to all DoD.
- Continued to work with OSW CADE team to implement data design and structure requirements and visual analysis tool
requirements into CADE system
- Integrated finalized products into CADE system repository for sharing with the Air Force and DoD cost community.

FY 2026 Plans:
- Continue efforts in support of the Cost Analysis Data Operating Model by prioritizing capability gaps for future development and
evaluating current CEM tools that would benefit by migration to an enterprise solution.
-Design, develop, and implement a series of robust, automated data pipelines integrated with dynamic analysis/predictive models,
custom applications, and conduct cost and technical studies for the cost estimating community, utilizing state-of-the-art data
science tools and ensuring that DAF cost estimating capabilities are leveraging modern toolsets and methods to the maximum
extent possible
-Collect historical program data to fill gaps against defined data collection requirements from previous year efforts and integrate
historical data collected into CADE system for central access to all DoD.
- Direct research to develop integrated datasets with embedded CERs and benchmarks, but with structures that let cost analysts
easily and quickly re-normalize data for specialized relationships and benchmarks.
- Initiate studies that are topical/timely or surface from prior research.
- Continue to work with OSW CADE team to implement data design and structure requirements as well as visual analysis tool
requirements into CADE system.
- Conduct reviews with technical/cost teams and quarterly contractor progress reviews with the government cost team.
FY 2027 Plans:

Operational Systems Development

