Title: Advanced Technology                                                                                                               7.916     13.985          6.946
Description: Advanced Technology/Pre-Tech includes efforts to mature technology for future GPS receivers identified in the
MGUE CDDs. These efforts aim to find innovative solutions to increase resiliency in GPS performance and improve on size,
weight, power, and cost (SWAP/C) of military receivers.

FY 2025 Plans:
Continue with the integration of Modernized Protection Device (MoPD) software into a Multi Global Navigation Satellite System
(MGNSS) software defined radio platform. Support MGNSS receiver security certification activities, specifically related to Regional
Military Protection (RMP) and extended PRN codes added capabilities. Build on FY 2024 multi-GNSS advancements in resilience
and assurance algorithms by developing standard metrics and test methodologies that enable unique implementations to be
compared / measured. Utilize algorithms implemented on Global Navigation Satellite System Test Architecture (GNSSTA) as well
as Open Service receivers for international partners to validate standard metrics and test methodologies. In coordination with
international partners, perform platform integration and Anti-Jam (AJ) performance demonstration of IMAS on a Unmanned Aerial
Vehicles (UAV) and/or Unmanned ground vehicles (UGV). Support evaluation of the Modernized Underwater Navigation System-
M-Code (MUNS-M) with US and allied stakeholders. Investigate developing a hardware implementation to complement the MoPD
software capable of meeting existing program protection profiles.
FY 2026 Plans:
Continue MoPD development to reduce non-recurring engineering costs associated with adding new capabilities to the military
Global Positioning System (GPS) receivers, such as open multi-Global Navigation Satellite System (GNSS) signals, advanced
signal processing, machine-learning anti-spoof algorithms, and anti-jam signal processing techniques. Investigate new crypto key
architectures and techniques for use in military/civil GPS receivers. Investigate incorporating Micro-Electro-Mechanical Systems
(MEMS) into GPS receiver architectures for improved accuracy and resiliency. Partner with allies on new Project Arrangements

