Title: Information Assurance, Security/Compatibility Certification, and Test/Evaluation                                                 15.992     17.970         11.851
Description: Develop, implement, and maintain Global Positioning System (GPS) security programs. Develop policy, strategy
and resource requirements for GPS User Equipment, security certification and compatibility certification. Security certification,
compatibility certification, and security approval ensures future military GPS receivers protect Critical Program Information (CPI)
and continue working in all environments and concepts of operations called for by U.S. Strategic Command (USSTRATCOM).

FY 2025 Plans:
Continue to conduct initial and delta security certification activities for all M-Code receivers, as required. Continue modernized
security evaluations/tests for Selected Availability Anti-Spoofing Module (SAASM) and other legacy GPS receiver equipment.
Review, approve, and track SAASM, M-Code receivers, and certified legacy receiver certified platforms and integrated
applications for all of DoD. Continue technical support to develop, validate and process engineering changes. Continue SAASM
and modernize KLIF effort. The KLIF facilitates the programming of black key (cryptographic) algorithms into the SAASM to

