Title: MGUE Inc 2 Miniature Serial Interface (MSI) Receiver Card Rapid Prototyping                                                      197.451    199.595         98.515
Description: The MGUE Inc 2 program will develop M-Code receiver technology for additional applications (space receivers,
precision guided munitions, and handheld receivers) to meet Service requirements. MGUE Inc 2 MSI Receiver Card Rapid
prototyping builds on the Application-Specific Integrated Circuit (ASIC) post-Preliminary Design Review (PDR) progress and will
develop, integrate, produce, and test M-Code capable, low size and power GPS MSI form factor to include a Next Gen ASIC.
The MSI receiver card is to meet the needs of low size, weight and power (SWaP) ground-embedded users. However, the Next
Gen ASIC must meet the needs of the MSI form factor and be backwards compatible with Inc 1 performance requirements as a
potential functional replacement due to Inc 1 ASIC obsolescence.

