C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                   FY 2024     FY 2025      FY 2026
Title: Space Warfighting Analysis Center (SWAC)                                                                                          97.686     121.409      125.982
Description: Space Warfighting Analysis Center is the foundational element to develop and provide authoritative Force Design
recommendations for the United States Space Force (USSF).

FY 2025 Plans:
Expand research studies, system design analysis, and wargaming integration prototyping demonstrations across a variety of
domains and mission areas to inform USSF force designs. The Multi-Domain Sensing Program will update MTI analysis findings
and initiate an MTI ground system study; expand the Kill Chain analysis to address additional joint needs; assess emerging
MWTD targets, threats, and enhanced sensing concepts; and begin a Space Based Environmental Monitoring Force Design
study. The Spectrum Warfare focus areas will continue developing the Government Reference Architectures and Capability Area
designs for Broadband, Narrowband, and Space to Space Force Designs, and will work on moving into space-based Position,
Navigation, and Timing (PNT) Force Designs with deeper inclusion into kill-webs. Additionally, Spectrum Warfare will continue
to study Ground Entry Point architecture for space network and Data Transmit and Receive Network support of high-altitude
mesh for Ground Data Network Force Designs, and begin developing a blueprint and Force Designing for Nuclear Command,
Control, and Communications. The Joint Sensitive Space Staff (JS3) will continue to conduct modeling, simulation and analysis of
satellite signatures to include sensing, communications and offensive and defensive space operations. The JS3 will also analyze
thresholds of detectability and provide concept of operations and tactics recommendations to inform future capabilities. Funds will
also enable execution of mission support areas that are required for daily operations.
FY 2026 Plans:

C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                     FY 2024    FY 2025      FY 2026
(U) Fiscal Year 2026 enables the continuation of comprehensive Force Design analyses to assess future requirements informed
by strategic guidance, threats, warfighter needs, and technology opportunities, tested through integrated modeling and analysis
and experimentation and validated through physics-based, data-driven analysis. SWAC efforts address the following three
areas: Integration, Multi-Domain Sensing and Spectrum Warfare. SWAC Integration efforts will establish USSF best practices for
conducting the full scope of force design analysis (e.g., mission area, capability area, and capability enabling), ensure integration
of SWAC analytical agendas and design recommendations, support and execute integrated analysis leveraging robust modeling
and dynamic coding. SWAC Integration will produce cost analysis and modeling methodology for studies and implement and
maintain support infrastructure and information Technology. The Multi-Domain Sensing Program (MDSP) will define options to
incorporate multiple phenomenology sensing to address warfighters' needs to maintain custody of moving targets on the ground,
at sea, and in the air. Additionally, MDSP will evaluate options for the space and ground missile warning architecture to best
support deterrence and ensure the survivability and endurability of the architecture through all phases of conventional and nuclear
conflict. The Spectrum Warfare Program (SWP) Space Data Network (SDN) effort will refine and deliver design recommendations
for space-based broadband and narrowband transport to both terrestrial and space-to-space users, to include NC3 capabilities.
The SWP Navigation Warfare effort will refine the near-term "Resilient GPS” reference architecture and expand to longer term
recommendations about GPS 4 and other Position, Navigation, and Timing capabilities. Lastly, the SWP Ground Data Network
effort will deliver recommendations on global terrestrial data transport, processing, and C2 that seamlessly interfaces with the
SDN. Analyzing options to leverage commercial and international partners is a significant part of all SWP efforts.
FY 2025 to FY 2026 Increase/Decrease Statement:
The FY 2026 request was reduced by 3.630 million for Advisory and Assistance Services to promote efficiencies and advance the
policies of the Administration in alignment with Executive Order 14222, "Implementing the President's Department of Government
Efficiency Cost Efficiency Initiative."

FY2025 to FY2026 funding increased due to work force optimization adjustments.
