B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                          FY 2024      FY 2025       FY 2026
Continue development, integration and testing of the USSF DEE with Integration Execution activities and MLS/cross-domain
solution (CDS) prototypes. These prototypes will update the Government Reference Architecture (GRA) for USSF DEE to begin
integration between acquisition and operational databases, and add additional programs into USSF DEE from across SSC.

Implement continuous system monitoring and security procedures to maintain Continuous Authority to Operate (cATO)
cybersecurity accreditation for MLS infrastructure.

Begin to scale DEE MVP access for a subset of 3000 users across the USSF. This includes increasing the capacity of user
access to each of the designated environments associated with each Impact Level (IL) (i.e., CUI, Secret, TS/SCI, and SAP). This
slow and deliberate scaling is a necessary step toward USSF-wide adoption.

Develop and initiate training roadmaps and curriculum for the acquisition force and capability development partners that will
increase overall enterprise digital proficiency. This training is key to decreasing the time it takes for acquisition professionals
to become accustomed to standardized workflows and processes and software toolsets across different program offices and
organizations within the USSF.
FY 2026 Plans:
Mature and complete development of four discrete MVP efforts and transition prototypes into a single enduring DEE architecture.
Mature MVP capabilities at multiple classification levels and scale from a user set of 2,000 to 10,000 across the space enterprise.
Continue integration with USAF Joint Simulation Environment (JSE) and leveraging of Operational Test, Training & Integration
(OTTI) capabilities to support readiness generation across space and Joint enterprise.

Leverage existing contract vehicles to enable DE and Integration for prototype infrastructure that allow for assessments and
capability solutions. Continue to prototype, develop, test and establish the Secure Containerized Facility, networks and systems,
tools, and DEE hosted on Hybrid cloud platform for cloud-computing and database storage.

Establish new contracts and funding to continue both existing and new facilities, networks, accreditation, DEE, digital tools,
MBSE, and modeling and analysis. Continue Special Access Program (SAP) DEE development and sustainment to support Cyber
operations, POM support planning, Kill Chain analysis, digital source selection, enterprise integration, intelligence, and penetration
testing.

Provide critical security elements across all domains to include facility, networks, DEE, systems, and tools. Security involves
physical security, information technology, and information assurance.



