B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                       FY 2024     FY 2025      FY 2026
Title: USSF Integrated Operations Network (ION)                                                                                               0.000      24.985        0.000
Description: The ION will provide a secure, reliable, multi-classification transport layer to support space missions. ION will be a
dynamic cloud-based software-defined mission network that integrates Space Force capabilities providing high bandwidth and
low latency for essential capabilities including support to Artificial Intelligence (AI) and the Unified Data Library (UDL). The USSF
Digital Engineering Ecosystem will be integrated into ION. Space Force discovered mission network infrastructure contained
significant technology debt and is initiating ION to better prepare for Great Power Competition.

FY 2025 Plans:
Develop a prototype hybrid agnostic transport and data interoperability to deliver software-defined mission architecture based on
Space Force kill webs addressing potential adversary operations.
FY 2026 Plans:
N/A
FY 2025 to FY 2026 Increase/Decrease Statement:
FY 2026 decreased by $24.985M due to ION funding transferring to Project 646602.
Title: SSC Developmental IT Infrastructure                                                                                                   19.908     19.020         20.966
Description: Space Systems Command (SSC) Developmental Information Technology (IT) Infrastructure, is a USSF initiative
that aims to drive effective, resilient, innovative, and cyber-secure solutions and IT across Space Systems Command, to meet
warfighter and business needs.

FY 2025 Plans:
Continue prior year developmental efforts, to include development of SSC Cybersecurity policies and guidance, capability
deployment, and pilot programs. After initial RDT&E efforts of Zero Trust (ZT) in FY 2024, further operational testing with various
PEOs such as Battle Management Command Control Communications (BMC3) and Space Domain Awareness and Combat
Power (SDA & CP) will be conducted with the Space Control Network (SCN) and mesh-ONE Terrestrial. SCRM capabilities will
be deployed to more USSF program offices and can monitor the entire USSF Industrial base with an estimated 20,000-30,000
suppliers. The Infrastructure Asset Pre-Approval (IA-Pre) program will continue development and commercial partnerships with
the satellite communication industry to ensure spectrum sharing will be secured and documented. Maintain support of SSC's
Approving Official and RMF capabilities, cybersecurity integration, and other vulnerability management and program protection
efforts. Furnish internal management of requirements, funding, contract actions, and PM support/training.
FY 2026 Plans:
Further expand ZT efforts to implement and test into more PEOs to demonstrate applicability to legacy and modernized systems.


