Remarks$$, $$In accordance with the approved SBEM Acquisition Strategy (Sep 2020), the Space Force will continue to address Joint SBEM gaps with a combination of DoD
materiel and non-materiel solutions, partnerships, and commercial, civil, and allied data. EWS will continue to use Other Transaction Authority (OTA) to competitively
pursue technological advancements in smaller sensor designs and leveraging commercial-based capabilities to develop the most optimal solution to long-term
Cloud Characterization and Theater Weather Imagery needs. The Phase II modernized pathfinder efforts will include OTA under Firm Fixed Price (FFP) contracts for
technology risk reduction and operational demonstration efforts, while minimizing developmental cost risks. FFP efforts under Phase II have resulted in considerable cost
savings for the government after conversion from Cost Plus, which enable the funding of the Ops Demo #2 launch vehicle within current budget profiles. The purpose
of Phase II is to explore various technology projects and partnerships to determine the most technically acceptable, resilient, and affordable option to support SBEM
acquisition strategy. Informed by Phase II, the SBEM acquisition strategy will include future EO/IR operational systems in FY26 and will consider modern architectures
such as proliferated-LEO, hosted-payload, or other commercial capabilities.

