Develop SBEM acquisition strategy to include future EO/IR acquisition, supported by SBEM architectural analysis, and informed
by previous Phase II prototype efforts and latest commercial industry investments to determine the most optimal solution to field
full operational systems to meet operational need dates.

Rapidly respond to implement system resiliency and situational awareness necessary to operate in the contested space domain.
Activities may include, but are not limited to program office support, studies, technical analysis, experimentation, prototyping, and
activities that may leverage commercial and international opportunities.
FY 2026 Plans:
Conduct Operational Demonstration #1 pre-ship review ahead of shipment of completed space vehicle to payload processing
facility for launch processing. Support launch and on-orbit checkout of General Atomics Ops Demo #1, characterizing its
performance to provide ops-quality data, meet SBEM EO/IR requirements for Cloud Characterization and Theater Weather
Imagery, while informing SBEM acquisition strategy for fielding full operational systems. Fund small launch vehicle through RSLP
OSP-4 contract to support Ops Demo #2 launch, currently slated for FY28, and provide support for Ops Demo #2 space vehicle
to launch vehicle integration study. Continue to invest for the development of commercial capabilities to address full SBEM Gap
requirements and Phase III activities. Develop options for remote ground station to support future GEO for persistent EO/IR
coverage of Indian Ocean region.

Rapidly respond to implement system resiliency and situational awareness necessary to operate in the contested space domain.
Activities may include, but are not limited to program office support, studies, technical analysis, experimentation, risk reduction,
prototyping, and activities that may leverage commercial, U.S. Government partnership, and international opportunities to respond
to existing and emerging adversarial threats with speed and agility.
FY 2025 to FY 2026 Increase/Decrease Statement:
FY 2026 increase due to Ops Demo #1 launch preparations/ramp up, build, and test activities; Ops Demo #2 launch funding.
