A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
Project 4026: Net-centric Sensor Analysis for Mine Warfare (NSAM) includes both the NSAM and Integrated Tactics projects. NSAM replaced the Organic Post
Mission Analysis (OPMA) system, which provides post mission analysis (PMA) capabilities for the Airborne Laser Mine Detection System (ALMDS), the Airborne Mine
Neutralization System (AMNS), and a separate module for contact management. Additionally, NSAM will replace the AN/AQS-20C interim Post Mission Analysis (iPMA)
system. NSAM will be the single tactical and environmental PMA system for all Mine Warfare (MIW) sensor data and will provide integrated contact management
capabilities. NSAM creates a collaborative, multi-data set, multi-user environment with the goal of reducing the mission timeline and increasing mission effectiveness.
NSAM is designed with an extensible architecture, to ease integration of additional sensors and advanced algorithms. The Integrated Tactics project develops tactics
at the MIW Staff and MCM Scenario level. Project provides new MIW tactics theory and Fleet tactics training for MIW Staffs. Theory and tactics are documented and
published into doctrine for Fleet users.

