Title: TacRS Initial Operations and Continuous Capability Development                                                                      28.958        30.052       33.282
Description: TacRS will leverage rapid, agile, and end-to-end acquisition processes to quickly evolve the design of future TacRS
missions. This approach will enable timely integration and readiness for launch call-up, Combatant Commander (CCMD) tasking,
and procurement of capabilities based on current threats and priorities.

FY 2025 Plans:

C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                     FY 2024   FY 2025       FY 2026
Support the planned launches and operations of the two VICTUS HAZE missions that will be ready for call-up in the second
quarter of FY 2025. Build on the VICTUS SOL satellite vehicle and ground investments made with prior year funding to initiate
the associated responsive launch service for VICTUS SOL in FY 2025 that could enable launch in the first half of FY 2026.
Begin acquisition planning efforts in FY 2025 for the future fourth VICTUS mission that will leverage lessons learned from
previous VICTUS missions and build upon the capabilities demonstrated in VICTUS NOX (launched in 2023), VICTUS SOL,
and VICTUS HAZE, where each VICTUS mission furthers the capability to launch within 24 hours of notice, match the orbital
plane of a previously unknown object, and conduct rendezvous and proximity operations for inspection and characterization
on an operationally relevant timeline. Continue development of an on-orbit pre-positioning demonstration to be able to support
a launch in FY 2026 that would evolve response force tasking to meet Combatant Command needs within 24 hours. Support
TacRS Range efforts that will provide necessary equipment and personnel to enable a responsive launch capability for all VICTUS
class missions. Continue to evolve new tactically responsive space capabilities that include launch, satellites, control systems,
and concept of operations using emerging and extant commercial launch and satellite providers. Rapidly respond to implement
system resiliency and situational awareness necessary to operate in the contested space domain. Activities may include, but are
not limited to technical analysis, experimentation, risk reduction, prototyping, program office support, studies, and activities that
may leverage commercial, U.S. Government partnership, and international opportunities to respond to existing and emerging
adversarial threats with speed and agility.
FY 2026 Plans:
Support the development, readiness, launch, and operations for the VICTUS HAZE, VICTUS SOL and other VICTUS missions.
The two maneuverable, prepositioned Space Domain Awareness (SDA) missions, VICTUS SURGO and VICTUS SALO, will
complete integration and testing in the second half of FY 2026. Support range efforts and ground infrastructure developments
that will provide necessary equipment, software, procedures and personnel to enable and support future TacRS missions.
Continue acquisition of future operational missions that require both rapid launch capabilities and maneuverable, prepositioned
capabilities. Support concept and capability development that enables the rapid use of commercial capabilities. Continue to evolve
new tactically responsive space capabilities that include launch, satellites, control systems, and concept of operations using
emerging and extant commercial launch and satellite providers while leveraging U.S. Government partnerships, and international
opportunities to respond to existing and emerging adversarial threats with speed and agility.

Rapidly respond to implement system resiliency and situational awareness necessary to operate in the contested space domain.
Activities may include, but are not limited to program office support, studies, technical analysis, experimentation, risk reduction,
prototyping, and activities that may leverage commercial, U.S. Government partnership, and international opportunities to respond
on tactically relevant timelines.
