Title: WGS - Global SATCOM Configuration Control Element (GSCCE) Modernization                                                       34.368       0.000        0.000
Description: WGS-GSCCE Modernization will improve the beam management panning ability for WGS-11 & 12 missions.
GSCCE is an existing ground system with Boeing that performs payload commanding at all five of the Wideband SATCOM
Operations Centers (WSOCs). WGS-GSCCE Modernization development upgrade will reduce commanding/commit time due
to increased commanding pace as a result of additional users/beams on WGS-11 & 12. This will result in the ability to rapidly

C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                      FY 2024    FY 2025      FY 2026
plan WGS-11 & 12 missions. In FY 2024, 33.038M of FY 2024 WGS BOOM funding, was re-allocated to GSCCE's core ground
modernization architecture to provide the baseline for BOOM enhancement.

FY 2025 Plans:
N/A
FY 2026 Plans:
N/A
Title: WGS - BOOM - Global SATCOM Configuration Control Element (GSCCE)                                                                        -       0.000         29.609
Description: WGS-BOOM-GSCCE is one of three BOOM development efforts to best improve the beam management panning
ability for WGS-11 & 12 missions. GSCCE is an existing ground system with Boeing that performs payload commanding at all five
of the Wideband SATCOM Operations Centers (WSOCs). WGS-BOOM-GSCCE development upgrade will reduce commanding/
commit time due to increased commanding pace as a result of additional users/beams on WGS-11 & 12. This will result in the
ability to rapidly plan WGS-11 & 12 missions.

FY 2025 Plans:
NA
FY 2026 Plans:
Leverage previous BOOM-GSCCE Enhancement deliverables to provide automation functions for payload planning/control in
support of WGS-11 & 12. FY26 design and development phase efforts will focus on advanced beam management and ensuring
mobile operations with tactically relevant timelines. Refactor GSCCE payload plan commit time, improve WSOC handover
times, and improve other GSCCE functionality for faster commanding of beam repoints supporting user movement in theater.
Implement risk mitigations, such as modifying legacy code or introducing new code and processes into a legacy system and
ensure compatibility. Ensure interfaces like CNPS and WSTARS are compatible with new GSCCE capability. Rapidly respond
to implement system resiliency and situational awareness necessary to operate in the contested space domain. Activities may
include, but are not limited to program office support, studies, technical analysis, experimentation, risk reduction, prototyping, and
activities that may leverage commercial, U.S. Government partnership, and international opportunities to respond to existing and
emerging adversarial threats with speed and agility.
FY 2025 to FY 2026 Increase/Decrease Statement:
FY 2026 increase to begin new start minimum viable WGS ground enhancement BOOM-GSCCE major thrust.
