E. Acquisition Strategy
Global SATCOM Configuration Control Element (GSCCE) modernization is a Cost Type contract modification using the engineering services CLIN on the current
contract where all versions of GSCCE software will merge to include WGS-1 thru -10 from ops and sustainment, Mitigation Anti-Jam Enhancement (MAJE), WGS-11,
and WGS-12 into one baseline version going forward along with studying architecture updates and recommending best approach for implementation in FY 2025-2027.
The end result will provide a GSCCE environment that sustains the current WGS 1-10 space vehicles along with an updated cyber posture and then also accounts for
the additional data needs required of WGS 11-12 within current operations. GSCCE modernization phase 1 is a special study and was awarded in September 2024 with
a study output in FY 2026 to inform phase 2; with a contract award in 4th quarter FY 2025.




