D. Acquisition Strategy
SSAEM post-launch and cal/val support contract is the sole-source contract to University Corporation Atmospheric Research (UCAR) due to their expertise in radio
occultation and space weather monitoring for the primary SSAEM sensors. The Justification & Approval (J&A) was approved in June 2018 and the Request for Proposal
was released on August 1st, 2018. The contract was initially awarded in July 2019 to provide post-launch cal/val and on-orbit support of its 5-year mission and with the
continued SSAEM performance beyond its design life, the contract has been extended to FY2028 to align with the updated space vehicles' mission life.




