A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
This project enables development of emerging capabilities for the maneuver force, that are envisioned by the Maneuver Center of Excellence (MCoE), the Maneuver
Capabilities Development Integration Directorate (MCDID), the Science and Technology (S&T) community, industry partners or the acquisition workforce that may
provide the Soldier or Squad increased capability to "fight, win and survive, day and night, in a multi- domain environment now and tomorrow." This project also allows
pursuit of technology breakthroughs that challenge current technical solutions and have the potential for providing increased Soldier performance. This effort focuses
on capabilities that enable modernization of Soldier sensor and situational awareness devices, including features and enhanced solutions to detect, recognize and
identify targets, and to provide target acquisition and handoff. The integration of higher performing multi-spectral sensors with smart processing will provide adjusted
weapon sight reticles and leverage network connectivity for improved situational awareness/understanding. Additional project capabilities include advanced optical
components and assemblies and techniques for signature management, resiliency across the electromagnetic spectrum, and integration of a modular design structure
for target acquisition applications including support for wireless data transfer, passive range determination, technologies for working in a global positioning system
(GPS) contested environment, advanced GPS replacement technologies and mitigation of manned and unmanned threat sensor systems. This project also supports
efforts for improved power and energy utilization and optimization across the Soldier and small unit. This project includes costs for efforts associated with development,
certification, verification and validation of interface products into the Adaptive Squad Architecture (ASA). Funding in this project aligns with Army's priorities in support of
the National Defense Strategy.

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                        FY 2025           FY 2026     FY 2027
Title: Soldier Enhanced Sensing Capabilities                                                                                                   3.380             3.142       3.264
Description: Soldier Enhanced Sensing Capabilities provides for development and testing of next generation night vision and
situational awareness capabilities for day and night, providing enhanced imagery, runtime, and decision making. This effort
includes advanced processing pipelines using AI/ML to provide improved situational awareness and information overlays on the
End User Device and/or Soldier Borne Mission Command (SBMC) or similar extended reality devices. This effort also includes
analyzing similar domestic and foreign commercial technologies to enhance understanding of the current state of the art. Soldier
Enhanced Sensing Capabilities will also look at Soldier or Squad as a System to understand tradeoffs within sensing and
situational awareness capabilities, to include secure wireless/spectrum considerations, contested GPS/GNSS (Global navigation
satellite system) environments, weapon data integration, among others.

